race.comment: Time for the G1 feature now where OVERPASS (1) gets the nod. He was super in The Everest behind the World's Best Sprinter, sitting on the speed as a 40-1 pop and finishing just 1.5L off the winner. Maps to find the front from an inside barrier and his trial in Sydney recently was very good. Looks primed to win his third Winterbottom in-a-row. JOKERS GRIN (2) looks to have come back even better since winning The Quokka and defeating OVERPASS in April. The draw should see him within striking distance of his main rival on the turn and Carbery reunites with his good mate. Looks set to explode now and can extend his winning run. REY MAGNERIO (4) was a good thing licked during Cup week as the race favourite. Gets Pike in the saddle now and he hits this third-up and is set to peak here. Can play a leading role. LUANA MISS (11) creates interest as a 3YO in the race and can be finishing with a wet sail. OSCAR'S FORTUNE (3) is in good touch and has to be included.
